cs.SC, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.SY, cs.LO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithms for computing and solving bivariate polynomials and difference equations. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents an algorithm for deciding the summability of bivariate rational functions. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper deals with the complexity of solving univariate difference equations. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with difference operators and solving difference equations. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper presents a new criterion for deciding the summability of bivariate rational functions.
